
## Step 6: Git Commands - Step by Step

Follow these commands in order:

```bash
# 1. Create project folder on your computer
mkdir nse-stock-screener
cd nse-stock-screener

# 2. Create directory structure
mkdir -p src config .github/workflows

# 3. Copy your modified files into these folders
# - Copy modified script to src/screener.py
# - Copy config/settings.py
# - Copy requirements.txt
# - Copy .gitignore
# - Copy README.md

# 4. Initialize git repository
git init

# 5. Add all files to staging
git add .

# 6. Commit files
git commit -m "Initial commit: NSE Stock Screener v2"

# 7. Create main branch (usually already on main)
git branch -M main

# 8. Create develop branch for testing
git checkout -b develop

# 9. Create feature branch for changes
git checkout -b feature/cloud-mode

# 10. Make any changes, then commit
git add .
git commit -m "Add cloud mode support"

# 11. Merge back to develop
git checkout develop
git merge feature/cloud-mode

# 12. Now push to GitHub (create repo on GitHub first!)
# First, create a new repository on GitHub website (don't add README there)

# 13. Add remote origin
git remote add origin https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/nse-stock-screener.git

# 14. Push main branch
git push -u origin main

# 15. Push develop branch
git push -u origin develop

# 16. Create a tag for version 1.0
git tag -a v1.0 -m "First stable release"
git push origin v1.0
